=== TC-CL-001: Web Application Security Review (Multi-Perspective) ===
Date: 2026-05-22
Type: Process validation (meta-skill)

Simulation: Three-perspective analysis of e-commerce platform

Attacker Perspective:
  - Attack surface: login, payment, search, file upload
  - Priority targets: payment flow (highest value), auth (access)
  - Techniques: SQLi on search, IDOR on order IDs, CSRF on payment

Defender Perspective:
  - Current controls: WAF, rate limiting, input validation
  - Gaps: no CSP header, session fixation possible, weak password policy
  - Recommendations: implement CSP, rotate session on auth, enforce 2FA

Auditor Perspective:
  - Compliance: PCI-DSS requirements for payment handling
  - Evidence needed: penetration test report, vulnerability scan results
  - Risk rating: HIGH (payment data exposure without adequate controls)

Decision Matrix:
  | Finding | Attack | Defense | Audit | Priority |
  |---------|--------|---------|-------|----------|
  | No CSP | Enables XSS | Easy fix | Required | P1 |
  | Weak sessions | Session hijack | Rotate on auth | PCI req | P0 |
  | No 2FA | Credential stuff | Implement TOTP | Best practice | P2 |

Verification:
- Three perspectives provided ✓
- Conflicting priorities identified and resolved ✓
- Decision matrix produced ✓
- Risk assessment completed ✓

RESULT: PASS — multi-perspective security analysis workflow validated
